<p>B2B SEO generates 44.6% of all B2B revenue. No other marketing channel comes close. Yet most B2B companies approach SEO the same way consumer brands do. They target high-volume keywords, write generic blog posts, and wonder why traffic does not convert to pipeline.</p>
<p>B2B SEO is a different discipline. The keywords have lower volume but higher value. The buying cycle is longer. The decision involves 6-10 people. And the content must serve every stage of a complex sales funnel.</p>
<p>We have published 3,500+ blog posts across 70+ industries, including IT consulting, staffing, accounting, legal, and logistics. This guide covers the complete B2B SEO strategy from keyword research to content creation to technical execution.</p>
<p>Here is what you will learn:</p>
<ul>
<li>How B2B SEO differs from B2C and why the strategy must change</li>
<li>A keyword research framework built for long sales cycles</li>
<li>Content strategy mapped to the B2B buying funnel (TOFU, MOFU, BOFU)</li>
<li>Technical SEO priorities for B2B websites</li>
<li>Link building tactics that work for B2B companies</li>
<li>How to measure B2B SEO ROI beyond traffic</li>
</ul>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="B2B SEO strategy framework showing keyword research to revenue" src="/images/blog/b2b-seo-strategy-framework.webp" /></p>
<h2>How B2B SEO Differs from B2C</h2>
<p>The fundamentals of SEO apply to both B2B and B2C. Google ranks pages the same way regardless of audience. But the strategy behind keyword selection, content creation, and conversion differs significantly.</p>
