<h2>B2B Content Strategy: Mapping Content to the Funnel</h2>
<p>The most effective B2B content strategy starts at the bottom of the funnel and works upward. Convert existing demand before trying to create new demand.</p>
<h3>Bottom of Funnel (BOFU). Convert</h3>
<p>BOFU content targets buyers who are ready to purchase. These pages generate the highest-value leads.</p>
<p><strong>Content types:</strong>
- Competitor comparison pages ("[Your Product] vs [Competitor]")
- Pricing pages with transparent cost breakdowns
- Case studies with specific results and ROI data
- Product demo landing pages
- Customer testimonial compilations</p>
<p><strong>Keywords:</strong> "[product] pricing," "[product] alternatives," "[product] vs [competitor]," "[product] review"</p>
<p>BOFU content has the lowest traffic but the highest conversion rate. A comparison page with 500 monthly visits that converts at 8% generates more pipeline than a blog post with 10,000 visits converting at 0.1%.</p>
<h3>Middle of Funnel (MOFU). Evaluate</h3>
<p>MOFU content helps prospects compare options and evaluate approaches.</p>
<p><strong>Content types:</strong>
- Buyer guides and selection frameworks
- ROI calculators and assessment tools
- Industry reports with original data
- Webinar recordings and workshop content
- Best-of lists and tool comparisons</p>
<p><strong>Keywords:</strong> "best [solution] for [industry]," "how to choose [product category]," "[solution] buyer guide"</p>
<p>For more on building comparison content, see our <a href="/blog/content-marketing-strategy/">content marketing strategy guide</a>.</p>
<h3>Top of Funnel (TOFU). Educate</h3>
<p>TOFU content attracts prospects who do not yet know your brand. This content builds authority and captures early-stage search demand.</p>
<p><strong>Content types:</strong>
- Educational guides and how-to articles
- Industry statistics and data reports
- Glossary pages defining industry terms
- Problem-focused blog posts
- Thought leadership and opinion pieces</p>
<p><strong>Keywords:</strong> "what is [concept]," "how to [solve problem]," "[industry] statistics," "[topic] guide"</p>
<p>B2B marketers who blog generate <a href="https://www.salesforce.com/marketing/b2b-automation/b2b-marketing-guide/b2b-content-marketing/">67% more leads</a> than those who do not. Consistent TOFU publishing builds the topical authority that lifts MOFU and BOFU pages.</p>
<h3>Content Mix for B2B</h3>
<p>The ideal publishing mix for most B2B companies:</p>
