<h3>The ROI Math</h3>
<p>B2B SEO delivers a <a href="/blog/seo-roi-statistics/">median ROI of 748%</a>. Here is how to calculate yours:</p>
<p><strong>SEO ROI = (Revenue from Organic Leads - SEO Investment) / SEO Investment x 100</strong></p>
<p>Example:
- Monthly SEO investment: $5,000 (content + tools + team time)
- Organic leads per month: 50
- Lead-to-customer rate: 5%
- Average deal value: $25,000
- Monthly revenue from SEO: 50 x 0.05 x $25,000 = $62,500
- Monthly ROI: ($62,500 - $5,000) / $5,000 = 1,150%</p>
<p>The compounding effect makes this even stronger. Content published in month 1 still generates leads in month 12. SEO customer acquisition cost decreases 60% over 2 years.</p>
<p>For more on tracking SEO performance, see our <a href="/blog/seo-kpis-guide/">SEO KPIs guide</a>.</p>
<h2>B2B SEO and AI Search in 2026</h2>
<p>B2B SEO now extends beyond Google. AI search platforms (ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews) are changing how buyers research solutions.</p>
<h3>What Changed</h3>
<p>AI Overviews and generative search reduce clicks for informational queries. But they increase the value of being cited as a trusted source. When ChatGPT recommends your product in response to "best project management software for agencies," that recommendation carries more weight than a page-1 ranking.</p>
<h3>How to Optimize for AI Search</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Publish authoritative, well-sourced content.</strong> AI models cite content that demonstrates expertise and includes verifiable data.</li>
<li><strong>Use clear, structured formatting.</strong> Tables, numbered lists, and FAQ sections make content easier for AI to parse and cite.</li>
<li><strong>Build entity authority.</strong> Consistent brand mentions across trusted sites teach AI models to recognize your brand as a topic authority.</li>
<li><strong>Maintain a strong <a href="/blog/on-page-seo-guide/">on-page SEO foundation</a>.</strong> AI search still indexes from the same web. Pages that rank well in Google get cited more in AI answers.</li>
</ul>
<p>The B2B companies winning in 2026 optimize for both traditional rankings and AI citations. The strategy is the same: publish expert-level content consistently. The distribution channels have expanded.</p>
